[2] Nigeria (Sokoto, Adamawa states)
Date: Mon 16 Aug 2021
Source: The Nation Online [edited]
https://thenationonlineng.net/cholera-kills-39-in-sokoto/


Cholera has so far killed 39 people in the last 3 weeks in 18 out of the 23 local government areas of Sokoto State, a top government official has confirmed. The Commissioner for Health, Dr Ali Inname disclosed this to reporters on [15 Aug 2021] in Sokoto while giving an update on the epidemic ravaging the state. According to Inname, 23 out of the casualties were recorded in the 1st 2 weeks of the epidemic, while the remaining 16 deaths were recorded in the past week.

He stated that Yabo, Dange/Shuni and Gwadabawa local government areas have continued to record active cases of the disease. The Commissioner further disclosed that his ministry has constituted 3 rapid response teams that were already fully operational. Inname also said the state government had stockpiled adequate intravenous fluids, drugs, and other related medicaments which were being distributed to all the affected local government areas. He also said the ministry was conducting a statewide immunization against cholera as part of efforts to stem the tide of the disease.

He added: "Scientifically, this problem may not completely abate until the current rainy season subsides. So, there is the need for the people to continue to ensure personal and environmental hygiene as well as heed to all medical advice issued by health professionals."

In a related development, cholera cases have risen to 63 in Adamawa State, the state Ministry of Health and Human Service said, adding that the numbers are increasing every day.

[Byline: Adamu Suleiman, Onimisi Alao]

