[3] Nigeria (Plateau State)
Date: Thu 12 Aug 2021
Source: The Nation [edited]
https://thenationonlineng.net/plateau-records-28-new-deaths-1415-cases-of-cholera/


Plateau has recorded 28 new deaths and 1415 cases following the outbreak of cholera in the State. Chairman House Committee on Health, Hon. Daniel Nanbol Listick, made this known to reporters in Jos on [Thu 12 Aug 2021]. Listick said as of [10 Aug 2021], based on the epidemiology data of cholera outbreak in the State, 16 local governments were affected with 1415 cases recorded. He added Jos North has the highest number of cholera with 599 cases while Jos South and Bassa local governments followed with 423 and 151 cases respectively.

He also added other local governments affected include: Bokkos 58; Kanam 41; Shendam 30; Wase 26; Langtang North 23; and Jos East 20.
Others include Riyom 14; Barkin Ladi and Kanke 9 cases, while Pankshin 7, Quapan and Langtang South 2 each, and Mangu has one case.

[Byline: Kolade Adeyemi]

